      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OUR LADY PEACE (6) is deep into her preparation and has her hoof on the till at start seven. Three weeks between runs when she savaged the line in the heavy going to finish a close-up second over 1000m at Kembla Grange. Can race a touch closer today and prove hard to hold out. TERRA LUMINA (7) is improving with racing and should be at his top for this from the good gate. Sat midfield and wasn't that far away with a tidy fourth over 900m at Newcastle. Finds a very weak contest and can figure prominently. SPARE (2) looked to have the race won on debut when he loomed strongly only to be nailed on the line for a head second over 1100m at Bathurst. Further improved for this and not to be underestimated. AVALON (3) Maurice filly from the good producing mare No Comment on debut for the Kim Waugh yard. Will handle the soft conditions and the trials have been okay.",
